# Core Plugin Principles

- **Single Responsibility**: Each plugin should have one clear, focused purpose
- **WordPress APIs First**: Use built-in WordPress APIs (Settings, Options, Transients, HTTP) over custom solutions
- **Hooks Over Modifications**: Never modify WordPress core files - always use hooks and filters
- **Namespace Everything**: Use unique prefixes/namespaces to avoid conflicts with other plugins
- **Conditional Loading**: Load code only when needed (admin vs frontend, specific pages)
- **Check Dependencies**: Verify required plugins/PHP/WordPress versions before executing
- **Performance**: Minimize impact on site speed through efficient code and caching
